   163	class Qwen2_5_VisionMLP(nn.Module):
   164	
   165	    def __init__(self,
   166	                 in_features: int,
   167	                 hidden_features: int,
   168	                 bias: bool = False,
   169	                 act_fn: Callable[[torch.Tensor], torch.Tensor] = F.silu,
   170	                 quant_config: Optional[QuantizationConfig] = None,
   171	                 prefix: str = ""):
   172	        super().__init__()
   173	        self.gate_proj = ColumnParallelLinear(in_features,
   174	                                              hidden_features,
   175	                                              bias=bias,
   176	                                              quant_config=quant_config,
   177	                                              prefix=f"{prefix}.gate_proj")
   178	        self.up_proj = ColumnParallelLinear(in_features,
   179	                                            hidden_features,
   180	                                            bias=bias,
   181	                                            quant_config=quant_config,
   182	                                            prefix=f"{prefix}.up_proj")
   183	        self.down_proj = RowParallelLinear(hidden_features,
   184	                                           in_features,
   185	                                           bias=bias,
   186	                                           quant_config=quant_config,
   187	                                           prefix=f"{prefix}.down_proj")
   188	        self.act_fn = act_fn
   189	
   190	    def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor):
   191	        x_gate, _ = self.gate_proj(x)
   192	        x_gate = self.act_fn(x_gate)
   193	        x_up, _ = self.up_proj(x)
   194	        x_down, _ = self.down_proj(x_gate * x_up)
   195	        return x_down

   198	def all_gather_interleave(local_tensor, hidden_size: int, tp_size: int):
   199	    """All-gather the input tensor interleavely across model parallel group."""
   200	    import torch.distributed as dist
   201	    gathered_tensors = [torch.zeros_like(local_tensor) for _ in range(tp_size)]
   202	    dist.all_gather(gathered_tensors,
   203	                    local_tensor,
   204	                    group=parallel_state.get_tp_group().device_group)
   205	
   206	    gathered_tensors_split = [
   207	        torch.split(tensor, hidden_size // tp_size, -1)
   208	        for tensor in gathered_tensors
   209	    ]
   210	    ordered_tensors = [
   211	        tensor for pair in zip(*gathered_tensors_split) for tensor in pair
   212	    ]
   213	    result_tensor = torch.cat(ordered_tensors, dim=-1)
   214	    return result_tensor

   219	    def __init__(
   220	        self,
   221	        embed_dim: int,

   227	        super().__init__()

   229	        self.tp_size = parallel_state.get_tensor_model_parallel_world_size()

   231	        self.hidden_size_per_attention_head = dist_utils.divide(

   236	        self.qkv = QKVParallelLinear(

   238	            head_size=self.hidden_size_per_attention_head,
   239	            total_num_heads=num_heads,
   240	            total_num_kv_heads=num_heads,
   241	            bias=True,
   242	            quant_config=quant_config,
   243	            prefix=f"{prefix}.qkv")
   244	        self.proj = RowParallelLinear(input_size=projection_size,
   245	                                      output_size=embed_dim,
   246	                                      quant_config=quant_config,
   247	                                      prefix=f"{prefix}.proj")

   249	        # Detect attention implementation.
   250	        self.attn_backend: _Backend = get_vit_attn_backend(support_fa=True)
   251	        if self.attn_backend not in {
   252	                _Backend.FLASH_ATTN, _Backend.TORCH_SDPA, _Backend.XFORMERS
   253	        }:
   254	            raise RuntimeError(
   255	                f"Qwen2.5-VL does not support {self.attn_backend} backend now."
   256	            )
   257	
   258	    def split_qkv(self, qkv: torch.Tensor) -> tuple[torch.Tensor, ...]:
   259	        # [s, b, 3 * head * head_dim]
   260	        seq_len, bs, _ = qkv.shape
   261	        if self.tp_size > 1:
   262	            qkv = all_gather_interleave(qkv, self.qkv.hidden_size,
   263	                                        self.tp_size)
   264	
   265	        # [s, b, 3 * head * head_dim] -> 3 * [s, b, head * head_dim]
   266	        q, k, v = qkv.chunk(3, dim=2)
   267	
   268	        # 3 * [s, b, head * head_dim]
   269	        if self.tp_size > 1:
   270	            splitter = partial(dist_utils.split_tensor_along_last_dim,
   271	                               num_partitions=self.tp_size)
   272	            q = splitter(q)[self.tp_rank]
   273	            k = splitter(k)[self.tp_rank]
   274	            v = splitter(v)[self.tp_rank]
   275	
   276	        # 3 * [s, b, head * head_dim] -> 3 * [s, b, head, head_dim]
   277	        new_shape = (seq_len, bs, self.num_attention_heads_per_partition,
   278	                     self.hidden_size_per_attention_head)
   279	        q, k, v = (x.view(*new_shape) for x in (q, k, v))
   280	        return q, k, v

   282	    def forward(
   283	            self,
   284	            x: torch.Tensor,
   285	            cu_seqlens: torch.Tensor,
   286	            rotary_pos_emb: torch.Tensor,

   289	    ) -> torch.Tensor:
   290	        # [s, b, c] --> [s, b, head * 3 * head_dim]
   291	        x, _ = self.qkv(x)
   292	
   293	        # [s, b, 3 * head * head_dim] -> 3 * [s, b, head, head_dim]
   294	        q, k, v = self.split_qkv(x)
   295	        batch_size = q.shape[1]
   296	
   297	        q, k, v = (rearrange(x, "s b ... -> b s ...").contiguous()
   298	                   for x in (q, k, v))
   299	        if rotary_pos_emb is not None:
   300	            q = apply_rotary_pos_emb_vision(q, rotary_pos_emb)

   302	
   303	        if self.attn_backend == _Backend.FLASH_ATTN:
   304	            # from vllm_flash_attn.flash_attn_interface import (
   305	            #   flash_attn_varlen_func)
   306	            from flash_attn import flash_attn_varlen_func
   307	
   308	            q, k, v = (rearrange(x, "b s ... -> (b s) ...") for x in [q, k, v])
   309	
   310	            output = flash_attn_varlen_func(q,
   311	                                            k,
   312	                                            v,
   313	                                            cu_seqlens_q=cu_seqlens,
   314	                                            cu_seqlens_k=cu_seqlens,
   315	                                            max_seqlen_q=max_seqlen,
   316	                                            max_seqlen_k=max_seqlen,
   317	                                            dropout_p=0,
   318	                                            causal=False)
   319	
   320	            context_layer = rearrange(output,
   321	                                      "(b s) ... -> b s ...",
   322	                                      b=batch_size)
   323	        elif self.attn_backend == _Backend.TORCH_SDPA:
   324	            # Execute attention entry by entry for speed & less VRAM.
   325	            outputs = []
   326	            for i in range(1, len(cu_seqlens)):
   327	                start_idx = cu_seqlens[i - 1]
   328	                end_idx = cu_seqlens[i]
   329	                q_i = q[:, start_idx:end_idx]
   330	                k_i = k[:, start_idx:end_idx]
   331	                v_i = v[:, start_idx:end_idx]
   332	                q_i, k_i, v_i = (rearrange(x, "b s h d -> b h s d")
   333	                                 for x in [q_i, k_i, v_i])
   334	                output_i = F.scaled_dot_product_attention(q_i,
   335	                                                          k_i,
   336	                                                          v_i,
   337	                                                          dropout_p=0.0)
   338	                output_i = rearrange(output_i, "b h s d -> b s h d ")
   339	                outputs.append(output_i)
   340	            context_layer = torch.cat(outputs, dim=1)
   341	        elif self.attn_backend == _Backend.XFORMERS:
   342	            from xformers import ops as xops
   343	            from xformers.ops.fmha.attn_bias import BlockDiagonalMask

   345	            attn_bias = BlockDiagonalMask.from_seqlens(q_seqlen=seqlens,
   346	                                                       kv_seqlen=None,
   347	                                                       device=q.device)
   348	
   349	            context_layer = xops.memory_efficient_attention_forward(
   350	                q, k, v, attn_bias=attn_bias, p=0, scale=None)
   351	        context_layer = rearrange(context_layer,
   352	                                  "b s h d -> s b (h d)").contiguous()
   353	
   354	        output, _ = self.proj(context_layer)
   355	        return output

   483	        self.register_buffer("inv_freq", inv_freq, persistent=False)
   484	        self._seq_len_cached = 0

   491	            self.inv_freq = 1.0 / (self.theta**(torch.arange(

   494	            seq = torch.arange(seqlen,
   495	                               device=self.inv_freq.device,
   496	                               dtype=self.inv_freq.dtype)
   497	            freqs = torch.outer(seq, self.inv_freq)
   498	            self._freqs_cached = freqs

import time
import torch

# Import the target module/classes
from vllm.model_executor.models.qwen2_5_vl import (
    Qwen2_5_VisionRotaryEmbedding,
    Qwen2_5_VisionTransformer,
)


def run_rotary_benchmark():
    dim = 64  # half head dim used in model
    emb = Qwen2_5_VisionRotaryEmbedding(dim)

    # Warmup
    _ = emb(128)

    t0 = time.perf_counter()
    _ = emb(1024)
    t1 = time.perf_counter()

    # Call again to measure cached path
    _ = emb(1024)
    t2 = time.perf_counter()

    print(f"rotary_first_build_ms={1000*(t1-t0):.3f}")
    print(f"rotary_cached_ms={1000*(t2-t1):.3f}")


def make_min_vision_config():
    # Minimal config object with required attributes for Qwen2_5_VisionTransformer
    class Cfg:
        patch_size = 14
        temporal_patch_size = 1
        in_channels = 3
        depth = 1
        hidden_size = 64
        num_heads = 4
        out_hidden_size = 64
        spatial_merge_size = 2
        window_size = 4
        fullatt_block_indexes = []
        intermediate_size = 128
        hidden_act = "silu"
    return Cfg()


def run_window_index_and_rotpos_benchmark():
    cfg = make_min_vision_config()
    vt = Qwen2_5_VisionTransformer(cfg)

    # Create a small batch of grid_thw: (grid_t, grid_h, grid_w)
    # Simulate 8x8 grid patches with t=1 for 4 images
    grid_thw = torch.tensor([
        [1, 8, 8],
        [1, 8, 8],
        [1, 8, 8],
        [1, 8, 8],
    ], dtype=torch.int32)

    # Warmup
    _ = vt.rot_pos_emb(grid_thw)
    _ = vt.get_window_index(grid_thw)

    t0 = time.perf_counter()
    _ = vt.rot_pos_emb(grid_thw)
    t1 = time.perf_counter()

    t2 = time.perf_counter()
    _ = vt.get_window_index(grid_thw)
    t3 = time.perf_counter()

    print(f"rot_pos_emb_ms={1000*(t1-t0):.3f}")
    print(f"get_window_index_ms={1000*(t3-t2):.3f}")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    run_rotary_benchmark()
    run_window_index_and_rotpos_benchmark()

def rot_pos_emb(self, grid_thw: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:
        # Cache pos_ids per unique grid to avoid recomputation
        key = tuple(tuple(map(int, row.tolist())) for row in grid_thw.cpu())
        pos_ids = self._pos_ids_cache.get(key)
        if pos_ids is None:
            pos_ids_list = []
            for t, h, w in grid_thw:
                h = int(h.item()) if isinstance(h, torch.Tensor) else int(h)
                w = int(w.item()) if isinstance(w, torch.Tensor) else int(w)
                t = int(t.item()) if isinstance(t, torch.Tensor) else int(t)
                hpos_ids = torch.arange(h, device="cpu").unsqueeze(1).expand(-1, w)
                wpos_ids = torch.arange(w, device="cpu").unsqueeze(0).expand(h, -1)
                hpos_ids = hpos_ids.reshape(
                    h // self.spatial_merge_size,
                    self.spatial_merge_size,
                    w // self.spatial_merge_size,
                    self.spatial_merge_size,
                ).permute(0, 2, 1, 3).flatten()
                wpos_ids = wpos_ids.reshape(
                    h // self.spatial_merge_size,
                    self.spatial_merge_size,
                    w // self.spatial_merge_size,
                    self.spatial_merge_size,
                ).permute(0, 2, 1, 3).flatten()
                pos_ids_list.append(
                    torch.stack([hpos_ids, wpos_ids], dim=-1).repeat(t, 1))
            pos_ids = torch.cat(pos_ids_list, dim=0).to(torch.long).contiguous()
            # store on CPU to reduce device-specific duplication
            self._pos_ids_cache[key] = pos_ids.cpu()
        else:
            # reuse cached CPU indices
            pos_ids = pos_ids
        max_grid_size = int(grid_thw[:, 1:].max().item())
        rotary_pos_emb_full = self.rotary_pos_emb(max_grid_size)
        pos_ids_dev = pos_ids.to(device=rotary_pos_emb_full.device)
        rotary_pos_emb = rotary_pos_emb_full[pos_ids_dev].flatten(1)
        return rotary_pos_emb

def get_window_index(self, grid_thw):
        # Cache window indices per unique grid to avoid recomputation
        key = tuple(tuple(map(int, row.tolist())) for row in grid_thw.cpu())
        cached = self._window_index_cache.get(key)
        if cached is not None:
            return cached
        window_index: list = []
        cu_window_seqlens: list = [0]
        window_index_id = 0
        vit_merger_window_size = (self.window_size //
                                  self.spatial_merge_size // self.patch_size)

        for grid_t, grid_h, grid_w in grid_thw:
            llm_grid_h = grid_h // self.spatial_merge_size
            llm_grid_w = grid_w // self.spatial_merge_size
            index = torch.arange(grid_t * llm_grid_h * llm_grid_w).reshape(
                grid_t, llm_grid_h, llm_grid_w)
            pad_h = vit_merger_window_size - llm_grid_h % vit_merger_window_size
            pad_w = vit_merger_window_size - llm_grid_w % vit_merger_window_size
            num_windows_h = (llm_grid_h + pad_h) // vit_merger_window_size
            num_windows_w = (llm_grid_w + pad_w) // vit_merger_window_size
            index_padded = F.pad(index, (0, pad_w, 0, pad_h), 'constant', -100)
            index_padded = index_padded.reshape(grid_t, num_windows_h,
                                                vit_merger_window_size,
                                                num_windows_w,
                                                vit_merger_window_size)
            index_padded = index_padded.permute(0, 1, 3, 2, 4).reshape(
                grid_t, num_windows_h * num_windows_w, vit_merger_window_size,
                vit_merger_window_size)
            seqlens = (index_padded != -100).sum([2, 3]).reshape(-1)
            index_padded = index_padded.reshape(-1)
            index_new = index_padded[index_padded != -100]
            window_index.append(index_new + window_index_id)
            cu_seqlens_tmp = seqlens.cumsum(0) * self.spatial_merge_unit + cu_window_seqlens[-1]
            cu_window_seqlens.extend(cu_seqlens_tmp.tolist())
            window_index_id += (grid_t * llm_grid_h * llm_grid_w).item()
        window_index = torch.cat(window_index, dim=0)
        result = (window_index, cu_window_seqlens)
        self._window_index_cache[key] = result
        return result

def get_window_index(self, grid_thw):
        # Cache window indices per unique grid to avoid recomputation
        key = tuple(tuple(map(int, row.tolist())) for row in grid_thw.cpu())
        cached = self._window_index_cache.get(key)
        if cached is not None:
            return cached
        window_index: list = []
        cu_window_seqlens: list = [0]
        window_index_id = 0
        vit_merger_window_size = (self.window_size //
                                  self.spatial_merge_size // self.patch_size)

        for grid_t, grid_h, grid_w in grid_thw:
            llm_grid_h = grid_h // self.spatial_merge_size
            llm_grid_w = grid_w // self.spatial_merge_size
            index = torch.arange(grid_t * llm_grid_h * llm_grid_w).reshape(
                grid_t, llm_grid_h, llm_grid_w)
            pad_h = vit_merger_window_size - llm_grid_h % vit_merger_window_size
            pad_w = vit_merger_window_size - llm_grid_w % vit_merger_window_size
            num_windows_h = (llm_grid_h + pad_h) // vit_merger_window_size
            num_windows_w = (llm_grid_w + pad_w) // vit_merger_window_size
            index_padded = F.pad(index, (0, pad_w, 0, pad_h), 'constant', -100)
            index_padded = index_padded.reshape(grid_t, num_windows_h,
                                                vit_merger_window_size,
                                                num_windows_w,
                                                vit_merger_window_size)
            index_padded = index_padded.permute(0, 1, 3, 2, 4).reshape(
                grid_t, num_windows_h * num_windows_w, vit_merger_window_size,
                vit_merger_window_size)
            seqlens = (index_padded != -100).sum([2, 3]).reshape(-1)
            index_padded = index_padded.reshape(-1)
            index_new = index_padded[index_padded != -100]
            window_index.append(index_new + window_index_id)
            cu_seqlens_tmp = seqlens.cumsum(0, dtype=torch.int32) * self.spatial_merge_unit + cu_window_seqlens[-1]
            cu_window_seqlens.extend(cu_seqlens_tmp.tolist())
            window_index_id += (grid_t * llm_grid_h * llm_grid_w).item()
        window_index = torch.cat(window_index, dim=0)
        result = (window_index, cu_window_seqlens)
        self._window_index_cache[key] = result
        return result

def make_min_vision_config():
    class Cfg:
        patch_size = 14
        temporal_patch_size = 1
        in_channels = 3
        depth = 1
        hidden_size = 64
        num_heads = 4
        out_hidden_size = 64
        spatial_merge_size = 2
        window_size = 4
        fullatt_block_indexes = []
        intermediate_size = 128
        hidden_act = "silu"
    return Cfg()


def bench_rotpos_and_window():
    cfg = make_min_vision_config()
    vt = Qwen2_5_VisionTransformer(cfg)

    grid_thw = torch.tensor([
        [1, 8, 8],
        [1, 8, 8],
        [1, 8, 8],
        [1, 8, 8],
    ], dtype=torch.int32)

    # Warmup
    _ = vt.rot_pos_emb(grid_thw)
    _ = vt.get_window_index(grid_thw)

    # Measure repeat usage (cache should help)
    t0 = time.time()
    for _ in range(50):
        _ = vt.rot_pos_emb(grid_thw)
    t1 = time.time()

    t2 = time.time()
    for _ in range(50):
        _ = vt.get_window_index(grid_thw)
    t3 = time.time()

    print(f"rot_pos_emb_repeat_50_ms={(t1-t0)*1000:.3f}")
    print(f"get_window_index_repeat_50_ms={(t3-t2)*1000:.3f}")

     - Added caches: self._pos_ids_cache and self._window_index_cache for reuse
  3) Qwen2_5_VisionTransformer.rot_pos_emb:
     - Added caching for pos_ids keyed by grid_thw, compute indices on CPU once and reuse; move to device only when indexing
  4) Qwen2_5_VisionTransformer.get_window_index:

- Notes:
  - The code already used torch.empty_like for all_gather buffers in all_gather_interleave and created inv_freq arange on CPU in __init__, so I focused on further buffer reuse and caching improvements and eliminating unnecessary recomputation.

import time
import torch

# Import the target module/classes
from vllm.model_executor.models.qwen2_5_vl import (
    Qwen2_5_VisionRotaryEmbedding,
    Qwen2_5_VisionTransformer,
)


def run_rotary_benchmark():
    dim = 64  # half head dim used in model
    emb = Qwen2_5_VisionRotaryEmbedding(dim)

    # Warmup
    _ = emb(128)

    t0 = time.perf_counter()
    _ = emb(1024)
    t1 = time.perf_counter()

    # Call again to measure cached path
    _ = emb(1024)
    t2 = time.perf_counter()

    print(f"rotary_first_build_ms={1000*(t1-t0):.3f}")
    print(f"rotary_cached_ms={1000*(t2-t1):.3f}")


def make_min_vision_config():
    # Minimal config object with required attributes for Qwen2_5_VisionTransformer
    class Cfg:
        patch_size = 14
        temporal_patch_size = 1
        in_channels = 3
        depth = 1
        hidden_size = 64
        num_heads = 4
        out_hidden_size = 64
        spatial_merge_size = 2
        window_size = 4
        fullatt_block_indexes = []
        intermediate_size = 128
        hidden_act = "silu"
    return Cfg()


def run_window_index_and_rotpos_benchmark():
    cfg = make_min_vision_config()
    vt = Qwen2_5_VisionTransformer(cfg)

    # Create a small batch of grid_thw: (grid_t, grid_h, grid_w)
    # Simulate 8x8 grid patches with t=1 for 4 images
    grid_thw = torch.tensor([
        [1, 8, 8],
        [1, 8, 8],
        [1, 8, 8],
        [1, 8, 8],
    ], dtype=torch.int32)

import time
import torch

# Import the target module/classes
from vllm.model_executor.models.qwen2_5_vl import (
    Qwen2_5_VisionRotaryEmbedding,
    Qwen2_5_VisionTransformer,
)


def run_rotary_benchmark():
    dim = 64  # half head dim used in model
    emb = Qwen2_5_VisionRotaryEmbedding(dim)

    # Warmup
    _ = emb(128)

    t0 = time.perf_counter()
    _ = emb(1024)
    t1 = time.perf_counter()

    # Call again to measure cached path
    _ = emb(1024)
    t2 = time.perf_counter()

    print(f"rotary_first_build_ms={1000*(t1-t0):.3f}")
    print(f"rotary_cached_ms={1000*(t2-t1):.3f}")


def make_min_vision_config():
    # Minimal config object with required attributes for Qwen2_5_VisionTransformer
    class Cfg:
        patch_size = 14
        temporal_patch_size = 1
        in_channels = 3
        depth = 1
        hidden_size = 64
        num_heads = 4
        out_hidden_size = 64
        spatial_merge_size = 2
        window_size = 4
        fullatt_block_indexes = []
        intermediate_size = 128
        hidden_act = "silu"
    return Cfg()


def run_window_index_and_rotpos_benchmark():
    cfg = make_min_vision_config()
    vt = Qwen2_5_VisionTransformer(cfg)

    # Create a small batch of grid_thw: (grid_t, grid_h, grid_w)
    # Simulate 8x8 grid patches with t=1 for 4 images
    grid_thw = torch.tensor([
        [1, 8, 8],
        [1, 8, 8],
        [1, 8, 8],
        [1, 8, 8],
    ], dtype=torch.int32)

    # Warmup
    _ = vt.rot_pos_emb(grid_thw)
    _ = vt.get_window_index(grid_thw)

    t0 = time.perf_counter()
    _ = vt.rot_pos_emb(grid_thw)
    t1 = time.perf_counter()

    t2 = time.perf_counter()
    _ = vt.get_window_index(grid_thw)
    t3 = time.perf_counter()

    print(f"rot_pos_emb_ms={1000*(t1-t0):.3f}")
    print(f"get_window_index_ms={1000*(t3-t2):.3f}")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    run_rotary_benchmark()
    run_window_index_and_rotpos_benchmark()

arguments.new_str:
def rot_pos_emb(self, grid_thw: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:
        # Cache pos_ids per unique grid to avoid recomputation
        key = tuple(tuple(map(int, row.tolist())) for row in grid_thw.cpu())
        pos_ids = self._pos_ids_cache.get(key)
        if pos_ids is None:
            pos_ids_list = []
            for t, h, w in grid_thw:
                h = int(h.item()) if isinstance(h, torch.Tensor) else int(h)
                w = int(w.item()) if isinstance(w, torch.Tensor) else int(w)
                t = int(t.item()) if isinstance(t, torch.Tensor) else int(t)
                hpos_ids = torch.arange(h, device="cpu").unsqueeze(1).expand(-1, w)
                wpos_ids = torch.arange(w, device="cpu").unsqueeze(0).expand(h, -1)
                hpos_ids = hpos_ids.reshape(
                    h // self.spatial_merge_size,
                    self.spatial_merge_size,
                    w // self.spatial_merge_size,
                    self.spatial_merge_size,
                ).permute(0, 2, 1, 3).flatten()
                wpos_ids = wpos_ids.reshape(
                    h // self.spatial_merge_size,
                    self.spatial_merge_size,
                    w // self.spatial_merge_size,
                    self.spatial_merge_size,
                ).permute(0, 2, 1, 3).flatten()
                pos_ids_list.append(
                    torch.stack([hpos_ids, wpos_ids], dim=-1).repeat(t, 1))
            pos_ids = torch.cat(pos_ids_list, dim=0).to(torch.long).contiguous()
            # store on CPU to reduce device-specific duplication
            self._pos_ids_cache[key] = pos_ids.cpu()
        else:
            # reuse cached CPU indices
            pos_ids = pos_ids
        max_grid_size = int(grid_thw[:, 1:].max().item())
        rotary_pos_emb_full = self.rotary_pos_emb(max_grid_size)
        pos_ids_dev = pos_ids.to(device=rotary_pos_emb_full.device)
        rotary_pos_emb = rotary_pos_emb_full[pos_ids_dev].flatten(1)
        return rotary_pos_emb

def make_min_vision_config():
    class Cfg:
        patch_size = 14
        temporal_patch_size = 1
        in_channels = 3
        depth = 1
        hidden_size = 64
        num_heads = 4
        out_hidden_size = 64
        spatial_merge_size = 2
        window_size = 4
        fullatt_block_indexes = []
        intermediate_size = 128
        hidden_act = "silu"
    return Cfg()


def bench_rotpos_and_window():
    cfg = make_min_vision_config()
    vt = Qwen2_5_VisionTransformer(cfg)

    grid_thw = torch.tensor([
        [1, 8, 8],
        [1, 8, 8],
        [1, 8, 8],
        [1, 8, 8],
    ], dtype=torch.int32)

    # Warmup
    _ = vt.rot_pos_emb(grid_thw)
    _ = vt.get_window_index(grid_thw)

    # Measure repeat usage (cache should help)
    t0 = time.time()
    for _ in range(50):
        _ = vt.rot_pos_emb(grid_thw)
    t1 = time.time()

    t2 = time.time()
    for _ in range(50):
        _ = vt.get_window_index(grid_thw)
    t3 = time.time()

    print(f"rot_pos_emb_repeat_50_ms={(t1-t0)*1000:.3f}")
    print(f"get_window_index_repeat_50_ms={(t3-t2)*1000:.3f}")

def bench_rotary_embed(dim: int = 64, seqlens=(512, 1024, 2048, 4096)):
    emb = Qwen2_5_VisionRotaryEmbedding(dim)

    times = []
    for s in seqlens:
        if torch.cuda.is_available():
            torch.cuda.synchronize()
        t0 = time.time()
        out = emb(int(s))
        if torch.cuda.is_available():
            torch.cuda.synchronize()
        t1 = time.time()
        _ = out[:1]
        times.append((s, t1 - t0))
    return times

        spatial_merge_size = 2
